=80=9CThat was very clear and concise,=E2=80=9D Welker responded.) Sanders,=
 appearing directly after Graham, offered more color. =E2=80=9CThis is what=
 authoritarianism is all about. It=E2=80=99s what dictatorship is all about=
,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CYou do not arrest elected officials who disagr=
ee with you, who undertake an investigation.=E2=80=9D <br/><br/>Of course, =
the prospect of politically motivated prosecutions=E2=80=94what Trump and h=
is allies have characterized as a revenge tour=E2=80=94was particularly sal=
ient this week, amid reports that the Biden administration has discussed of=
fering
preemptive blanket pardons to likely Trump targets. Schiff, who participate=
d in the January 6 investigation himself, is one such potential target, but=
 said he believed pardons would be =E2=80=9Cunnecessary=E2=80=9D because th=
e committee=E2=80=99s work was all above board. He also warned that =E2=80=
=9Cgiving preemptive blanket pardons on the way out of an administration I =
think is a precedent we don=E2=80=99t want to set.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Romney=
, too, is a possible target=E2=80=94he=E2=80=99s the only Republican senato=
r who voted to impeach Trump <i>twice</i>. But he told <b>Jake Tapper </b>h=
e wasn=E2=80=99t =E2=80=9Cparticularly worried about criminal investigation=
s,=E2=80=9D musing that Trump=E2=80=99s <i>they-oughta-be-in-jail</i> rheto=
ric might just be hyperbole. He then made a better-angels appeal. =E2=80=9C=
I think President Trump is likely to try and focus on the future,=E2=80=9D =
he added. =E2=80=9CPeople who committed crimes, I=E2=80=99m sure, will be p=
rosecuted. But I think that=E2=80=99s few and far between.=E2=80=9D<br/><br=
/>Meanwhile, the fallout from Biden=E2=80=99s pardon
of his son <b>Hunter</b> continues, even within his own party. Sanders call=
ed it =E2=80=9Ckind of a dangerous=E2=80=9D precedent =E2=80=9Cas a very wi=
